t\" foreign trade company, and\nelectronics and computers were chosen because there were no such products on\nthe Yugoslav market.\n\nGet started\n\nLearn more\n\nThe beginning itself was very modest. In a neglected space of a former fire\nstation, two engineers, two technicians, and 22 unskilled workers assembled\ntwo types of desktop computers based on Japanese documentation.\n\nGet started\n\nLearn more\n\n### The First Models\n\n### The First Models\n\nThe first models that came out of Digitron's production line were the desktop\ncalculators db 1200 and db 1212, but Digitron gained worldwide fame thanks to\nits \"little ones\", as the employees of Digitron affectionately called their\npocket calculators.\n\nGet started\n\nLearn more\n\nThe pocket calculator db 800 made history as the first European pocket\ncalculator, and its successor model db 801 received awards and recognition\nwherever it appeared.\n\nGet started\n\nLearn more\n\nOrsola City Gallery\n\nTrg Slobode (below the Buje City Museum), 52460 Buje, Croatia\n\nWORKING HOURS\n\nSaturdays: 10 AM - 13 PM\n\nIn the period from April 14th to August 18th during working days, from 9 AM to\n1 PM.\n\nAnnouncements of group visits and other inquiries available via telephone or\ne-mail.\n\nCONTACT\n\ntelephone: +385 052 773 075 e-mail: info@retrobit.net\n\nDevelopment of calculating devices\n\nAncient and Mechanical CalculatorsElectromechanical CalculatorsDigital\nCalculators\n\nDigitron and Buje\n\nAnd there was DigitronOn the technological throneThe Blossoming of BujeCulture\nand Sport\n\nVarious calculators and their stories\n\nCalculating in YugoslavianWorld Class PlayersCold War CalculationsUnusual\nUsesBack to the FutureImpressum\n\nAudio\n\nAudio\n\nStart AR\n\n", "frontpage": false}
